commitResults.messageBody: Added Ability to store tasks into List and retrieve the List

Added Task class,
Revamped List,
Added Checking task functionality

Added 3 subclasses ToDo, Deadline, Event
Implemented Functionality

Could be improved

Implemented Unique Error handling,

Rough and Rudimentary for now

Added Delete functionality,

Added More error handling

Set-up basic JUnit testing system

Tests DukeParser.parse() and DukeStorage.retrieve()

Fleshed out the TextUiTesting to include errors,
Added Java Docs

Duke now stores list data locally @ localList.txt

Duke can retrieve and create a txt file to store list data in the same location as the application

Classes have been updated to include another constructor to accommodate creation from txt file data

greeting() function updated to read localList.txt if present and return a List<Task> which contains locally store list data

close() function now saves current List<Task> to localList.txt if present, if not it will create a localList.txt file and save it there

Merged the 2 branches Level-7 and Level-8

Code was cleaned up by fixing bugs in: - the deadline and event class
- localList.txt retrieval code in greeting()

Code and logic was restructured into 4 new classes

DukeMain: Contains the main application and main function to run

DukeParser: Handles logic and understanding of user input

DukeUI: Handles User Interface related functions

DukeStorage: Handles Storage related functions to retrieve and save files

Sorted various classes into packages

tasks: Contains task class and subclasses

exception: Contains all created exceptions

Duke: Contains all Duke related functions and packages
Fleshed out JavaDocs for the functions in all the classes.

Implemented find [filter] that looks through the list of tasks to display tasks that contain filter in their descriptions

Added Functions in taskList, task to support

Added DukeUI functions to support
Looked for Coding Standard Errors in the code

Firmed up Date formats for Deadline and Event, requiring user to use a specific format to input a Date

Changed logic to check for right date format, and pass a LocalDate into the constructors of Deadline and Event

Deadline and Event classes changed to take LocalDate instead of String, and return a custom format when displaying
